ce:section.ce:para:
A number of reports published on drug delivery systems deploying various combinations of chitosan and carbon nanomaterials have been summarized including carbon nanotubes (Table 1
                     ), graphene (Table 2
                     ), nanodiamond, fullerene, and carbon quantum dots (Table 3
                     ). The current research is aiming to improve the surface functionalized forms of carbon nanomaterials through covalent and non-covalent grafting to chitosan and rediscover their applications. Based on these sources, it can be concluded that the preparation of nanocomposites encompassing chitosan and carbon nanoparticles with drug-delivery objectives usually does not entail complex reaction processes; it primarily requires a selection of appropriate materials and linkers that can improve the generation of more efficient nano-vessels.
